Commentary Text: Arshdeep Singh to Krunal Pandya, out Hooda Run Out!! 1 run completed . Hooda pays for his laxness. This was pulled to deep square and looked an easy two, but Hooda was taking it easy, the throw from Bairstow hits direct at the bowler's end and Hooda is caught short as he stretches to make it. Krunal Pandya understandably is upset with Hooda for that piece of running. Two quick wickets for PBKS. Replays show that Hooda was jogging and was not expecting the throw to come at his end. Commentary Text: Rabada to Rahul, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! This is a Test match dismissal. This good length delivery on off straightens and at pace, KL defends but it takes the outside-edge and is caught by a diving Jitesh Sharma to his right. That's a fine riposte after the cover-driven four. Rabada pulled the length back and was rewarded immediately with the pitch helping him a tad. Big wicket and Mayank celebrates knowing the importance of that one. Rahul c Jitesh Sharma b Rabada 6(11) [4s-1]

This was a normal leg-break with a bit of flight, Dhawan premeditated the slog sweep and plays all over it, the ball sneaks underneath the swinging blade and uproots middle-stump.
